          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0613P0_20000612_GCR_177' title='Link to this speech by Mr Robin Bridgeman' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-robin-bridgeman" title="Mr Robin Bridgeman">Viscount Bridgeman</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Before the noble Lord sits down, I request clarification. Does Clause 18 totally absorb my amendment?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0613P0-04642'>
        <a name='S5LV0613P0_20000612_GCR_178'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0613P0_20000612_GCR_178' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            The new clause is more restrictive than the noble Viscount's amendment.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0613P0-04643'>
